ighters risked their lives and those of their families to hide the men. Drawing on declassified files and eye-witness testimonies from across Europe and the United States, Helen Fry provides a significant reassessment of MI9’s wartime role. Central to its success were figures such as Airey Neave, Jimmy Langley, Sam Derry, and Mary Lindell—one of only a few women parachuted into enemy territory for MI9. This astonishing account combines escape and evasion tales with the previously untold stories behind the establishment of MI9—and reveals how the organization saved thousands of lives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xSearch and rescue operations. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xSecret servicezGreat Britain. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War II.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020z978311069231040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300255928423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300255928.jpg  a978-3-11-069231-0  YUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020